CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 12, 1966, pg. 1B reads: "Visiting Guests - Among the out of town guests of the Kappa Silhouettes Black and White Ball were the two couples pictured here. Left to right: Mr. and Mrs. Arthur Chandler of Washington, Pa., and Mr. and Mrs. Ray Claybrooks of Cleveland, Ohio.  All of the feminine guests wore either a black or white gown, or combined the two colors."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Mr. and Mrs. Arthur Chandler, posed in Penn Sheraton Hotel for Kappa Alpha Psi Silhouettes Black and White Ball
